<subSubSection id="4AB7D3D1FF80FFBBFF65FC0BFDDCFB8F" pageId="17" pageNumber="78" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0212805AFF80FFBBFF65FC0BFDDCFB8F" blockId="17.[136,1452,373,1228]" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF80FFBBFF65FC0BFE8FFC40" bold="true" box="[189,335,985,1011]" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">Distribution</emphasis>
:—This species has a wide distribution, occurring from 
<collectingCountry id="7ABAC0CAFF80FFBBFC08FC08FBE6FC47" box="[976,1062,986,1012]" name="Mexico" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to the south of 
<collectingCountry id="7ABAC0CAFF80FFBBFB06FC08FAE5FC47" box="[1246,1317,986,1012]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, where it is found in the states of Amazonas, 
<collectingRegion id="C0694EB8FF80FFBBFDDCFC2CFD88FBAB" box="[516,584,1022,1048]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C0694EB8FF80FFBBFD8CFC2CFD2FFBAB" box="[596,751,1022,1048]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C0694EB8FF80FFBBFD23FC2CFC5FFBAB" box="[763,927,1022,1048]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C0694EB8FF80FFBBFC73FC2CFB92FBAB" box="[939,1106,1022,1048]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C0694EB8FF80FFBBFB86FC2CFB13FBAB" box="[1118,1235,1022,1048]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C0694EB8FF80FFBBFB07FC2CFAEEFBAB" box="[1247,1326,1022,1048]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, and in the Distrito Federal (Goldenberg 2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4AB7D3D1FF80FFBBFF65FB97FF1AFB7F" pageId="17" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0212805AFF80FFBBFF65FB97FF1AFB7F" blockId="17.[136,1452,373,1228]" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF80FFBBFF65FB97FEFEFBEC" bold="true" box="[189,318,1093,1119]" pageId="17" pageNumber="78">Comments</emphasis>
:—In Marambaia, this species is restricted to Dense Submontane Ombrophilous Forest. It has discolour leaves with a dark green adaxial surface and a rufous abaxial surface, early caducous involucral bracts and bracteoles, and a dorsally gibbouos and callous connective with two latero-ventral lobes. Additional illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF80FFBBFAE8FB5CFF16FB7F" author="Baumgratz, J. F. A." pageId="17" pageNumber="78" pagination="69 - 86" refId="ref22438" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A. (1982) Miconias do Estado do Rio de Janeiro. Secao Tamonea (Aubl.) Cogniaux (Melastomataceae). Arquivos do Jardim Botanico do Rio Janeiro 26: 69 - 86." type="journal article" year="1982">Baumgratz (1982)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
